(75,"Crispy Fried Chicken","This is the ultimate recipe for the best crispy fried chicken, honed from years of experimenting and collecting tips. It emphasizes preparation and cooking method to achieve the perfect crispy texture.","00:15:00","00:35:00","4","medium","[\"Take your cut up chicken pieces and skin them if you prefer.\", \"Put the flour in a large plastic bag. Season the flour with paprika, salt, and pepper to taste.\", \"Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk then, a few at a time, put them in the bag with the flour, seal the bag and shake to coat well.\", \"Place the coated chicken on a cookie sheet or tray, and cover with a clean dish towel or waxed paper. LET SIT UNTIL THE FLOUR IS OF A PASTE-LIKE CONSISTENCY. THIS IS CRUCIAL!\", \"Fill a large skillet about 1/3 to 1/2 full with vegetable oil. Heat until VERY hot.\", \"Put in as many chicken pieces as the skillet can hold. Brown the chicken in HOT oil on both sides.\", \"When browned, reduce heat and cover skillet; let cook for 30 minutes. Remove cover, raise heat again, and continue to fry until crispy.\", \"Drain the fried chicken on paper towels. Depending on how much chicken you have, you may have to fry in a few shifts. Keep the finished chicken in a slightly warm oven while preparing the rest.\"]","2024-01-05 05:48:23","ca49ccb4-7cf0-4477-8f3f-90371e737b38",NULL,NULL,"2024-01-15 23:19:12","[{\"id\": 0, \"name\": \"chicken\", \"note\": \"4 pounds, cut into pieces\", \"unit\": \"whole\", \"amount\": \"1\"}, {\"id\": 1, \"name\": \"buttermilk\", \"unit\": \"cup\", \"amount\": \"1\"}, {\"id\": 2, \"name\": \"all-purpose flour for coating\", \"unit\": \"cup\", \"amount\": \"2\"}, {\"id\": 3, \"name\": \"paprika\", \"unit\": \"Teaspoon\", \"amount\": \"1\"}, {\"id\": 4, \"name\": \"salt and pepper\", \"unit\": \"Pinch\", \"amount\": \"2\"}, {\"id\": 5, \"name\": \"vegetable oil for frying\", \"unit\": \"quart\", \"amount\": \"2\"}]",0),
(76,"Easy Skillet Chicken Thighs","This Easy Skillet Chicken Thigh recipe with a simple garlic cream sauce is the perfect chicken dinner for easy weeknights or entertaining. Everyone loves this juicy chicken dish and it takes less than 30 minutes to make!","00:10:00","00:15:00","6","easy","[\"Use a paper towel to pat the chicken thighs dry.\", \"In a small bowl, combine the garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, salt, and black pepper. Rub the seasoning mixture all over the chicken thighs, on both sides.\", \"Heat a large cast iron to medium heat and add the olive oil.\", \"Place chicken thighs skin side down in the hot skillet and cook, until skin is crispy about 5 minutes, flip chicken thighs and cook for another 8 to 10 minutes or until internal temp is 165 degrees. Transfer chicken to a plate.\", \"Add the butter, shallot, and garlic to the skillet. Cook for 1 minute. Stir in the chicken broth, lemon juice, thyme, and red pepper flakes. Reduce heat to low and stir in the heavy cream. Simmer for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until sauce thickens up a bit.\", \"Place the chicken back in the pan with the sauce. Garnish with fresh parsley. Serve the chicken warm with the sauce.\", \"Store leftover chicken thighs in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.\"]","2024-01-08 03:05:31","ca49ccb4-7cf0-4477-8f3f-90371e737b38","null","null","2024-01-08 03:05:31","[{\"id\": 0, \"name\": \"boneless chicken thighs, about 1 1/2 pounds\", \"unit\": \"whole\", \"amount\": \"6\"}, {\"id\": 1, \"name\": \"garlic powder\", \"unit\": \"Teaspoon\", \"amount\": \"1/2\"}, {\"id\": 2, \"name\": \"onion powder\", \"unit\": \"Teaspoon\", \"amount\": \"1/2\"}, {\"id\": 3, \"name\": \"paprika\", \"unit\": \"Teaspoon\", \"amount\": \"1/2\"}, {\"id\": 4, \"name\": \"Kosher salt and black pepper\", \"unit\": \"whole\", \"amount\": \"to taste\"}, {\"id\": 5, \"name\": \"olive oil\", \"unit\": \"Tablespoon\", \"amount\": \"2\"}, {\"id\": 6, \"name\": \"butter\", \"u