(101,"Syrian Lentil Soup","A hearty and flavorful soup that is quick to make, perfect for serving with pita croutons and lemon wedges.","00:10:00","00:20:00","6-8","easy","[\"Add olive oil, onion, carrots, potato and 2 tsp kosher salt to a heavy-bottomed pot over medium heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 5-7 minutes.\", \"Add garlic, parsley, and pepper paste. Cook until fragrant, about another minute. Add lentils, 6 c of water and 3 tsp kosher salt (only 1 if using table salt). Bring to a boil, reduce to simmer, cover and cook until lentils have opened, about 20 minutes.\", \"Puree with a hand blender or transfer to an upright blender in batches. Adjust seasoning and serve with pita croutons and lemon wedges.\", \"Can be made up to 2 days ahead. Reheat before serving by stirring frequently over medium heat, uncovered, until just before boiling. You may need to add water if it\'s thickened after sitting.\"]","2024-03-10 19:31:39","b6f32b03-9d03-4ff9-8c06-08932e3d7940","{\"key\": \"a2c67a77-1e75-4b3f-bd02-59039b8f89c3-1xcj4q.jpeg\", \"url\": \"https://utfs.io/f/a2c67a77-1e75-4b3f-bd02-59039b8f89c3-1xcj4q.jpeg\", \"name\": \"IMG_5597.jpeg\", \"size\": 3506927}",NULL,"2024-03-10 19:33:32","[{\"id\": 0, \"name\": \"extra virgin olive oil\", \"unit\": \"Tablespoon\", \"amount\": \"2\"}, {\"id\": 1, \"name\": \"medium onion, chopped\", \"unit\": \"whole\", \"amount\": \"1\"}, {\"id\": 2, \"name\": \"carrots, peeled and chopped\", \"unit\": \"whole\", \"amount\": \"2\"}, {\"id\": 3, \"name\": \"small potato, peeled and chopped\", \"unit\": \"whole\", \"amount\": \"1\"}, {\"id\": 4, \"name\": \"garlic, smashed\", \"unit\": \"clove\", \"amount\": \"4\"}, {\"id\": 5, \"name\": \"chopped parsley\", \"unit\": \"cup\", \"amount\": \"1/2\"}, {\"id\": 6, \"name\": \"yellow or red lentils\", \"unit\": \"cup\", \"amount\": \"1\"}, {\"id\": 7, \"name\": \"Diamond Crystal kosher salt, divided (half if using table salt)\", \"unit\": \"Teaspoon\", \"amount\": \"5\"